How to Connect to plant network (external)  
1
2
Navigate to https://localhost  
Navigate to Data-Sender section with the main menu  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
1
3
Click "Network"  
4
If you want to make a static connection click 'Static' radio button  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
2
5
If you chose 'Static' insert IP address with mask class  
If you want to set multiple ip addresses separate them with a comma ','  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
3
6
Insert default gateway ip address  
7
Here you can choose one or multiple dns server  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
4
If you want to set multiple dns server separate them with a comma ','  
You can choose ethernet or wifi connection  
8
In order to establish a wifi connection you will need to insert a4GATE wireless  
adapter on a PCB external USB port  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
5
If you want to make a wifi connection you will need to specify wifi network ssid  
and password  
9
By clicking the droplist below you will see every wifi network found by a4GATE. If  
the list does not show your desired network please press 'Apply' button after set  
connection type to wifi and click the 'ReloadB'  
10  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
6
11 Select desired net  
12 If you want to connect to a hidden network you can always edit ssid manually  
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com  
7
If the selected network require a password you can insert it in this filed, otherwise  
you can leave it blank  
13  
If you prefere a DHCP connection click the 'DHCP' radio button. In this case you do  
not need to fill ip, default gateway or dns fields

Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com

15 Click "Save" button  
16 Click "Apply" button to "make it real"
